# How does Python execute a program?

Python source code is written in `.py` files.
The Python compiler checks source code syntax.
It converts source code into bytecode.
Bytecode is stored as `.pyc` files.
Python Virtual Machine loads the bytecode.
The interpreter executes bytecode instruction by instruction.
The program produces the required output.

## Execution Flow

```text
Source Code (.py)
        │
        ▼
Python Compiler
        │
        ▼
Bytecode (.pyc)
        │
        ▼
Python Virtual Machine (PVM)
        │
        ▼
Interpreter
        │
        ▼
Output
```

